{
  "_doc": "Single source of truth for code-owned geometry of atom-built 9-slice frames. Read by the candidate generator (scripts/nine-slice-kit.mjs), the in-app editor (NineSliceEditor), and the catalog edit-link (AssetLibraryStudio). Media inputs are fetched from backend-owned live slots into a temporary workspace; composed pixels are uploaded as private candidates and are never read from or written to Git. atoms names semantic source slots; variants[].out and line/lineTones[].out name semantic output slots; swap selects a palette; consume names the CSS variable driven by an accepted output; carve floods navy bleed outside the rail. A line is the transparent-interior twin assembled from corner and edge atoms so a surface remains visible behind its ornament; only edge-reaching bracket frames qualify (ADR-0034). lineTones apply semantic palette swaps while preserving the cool steel rail. kind='junction' derives tee/cross geometry by mirroring the corner into concave angles. kind='bar' builds a one-dimensional horizontal separator from edge and tee/corner geometry and is consumed with a horizontal border-image; barScale controls rail weight. Geometry and registry text live in Git; source and output pixels live only in backend storage.",
